><mn>2</mn><msup><mo>…</mo><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>×</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>…</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>ˆ</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>ˆ</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>798037</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>ˆ</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>798</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></math>(accept&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>45</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>°</mo></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> &nbsp;A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;If no working shown, award&nbsp;<strong><em>(A0)(M1)(A0)A0</em></strong>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>80</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></math>(or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>46</mn><mo>°</mo></math>)&nbsp;(2sf).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></math> be the midpoint of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>BC</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>BM</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp;(seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp; (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to use sine or cosine in triangle&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>BMV</mi></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>CMV</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>arc</mtext><mi>sin</mi><mtext> </mtext><mfrac><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mn>106</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math>&nbsp;</strong></em>OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mtext>arc</mtext><mi>cos</mi><mtext> </mtext><mfrac><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mn>106</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math>&nbsp;OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>399018</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>ˆ</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>798037</mn><mo>…</mo></math></strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>ˆ</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>798</mn></math></strong></em>&nbsp;(accept&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>45</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>°</mo></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> If no working shown, award <strong><em>(A0)(M1)(A0)A0</em></strong> for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>80</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></math>(or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>46</mn><mo>°</mo></math>)&nbsp;(2sf).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 3</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>VC</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>VB</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em> (A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p>attempt to use the cosine formula for an angle using two vectors representing the edges of triangle&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>BVC</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em> (M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mfenced><mn>3</mn></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><mfenced><mn>4</mn></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>9</mn><mfenced><mn>9</mn></mfenced></mrow><mrow><msqrt><msup><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt><msqrt><msup><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msup><mn>4</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mrow></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mn>74</mn><mn>106</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em> (A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>798037</mn><mtext>...</mtext></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>798</mn></math>&nbsp;(accept&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>45</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>°</mo></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>If no working shown, award<strong><em>&nbsp;(A0)(M1)(A0)A0</em>&nbsp;</strong>for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>80</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></math>(or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>46</mn><mo>°</mo></math>)&nbsp;(2sf).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 4</strong></p>\n<p><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mrow><mi>VC</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mrow><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr